WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.545 --> 00:00:02.546
[knocks]

2
00:00:05.715 --> 00:00:06.716
[colonel] Enter.

3
00:00:09.135 --> 00:00:10.135
[door closes]

4
00:00:15.934 --> 00:00:18.562
{\an8}Lieutenant Shaw reporting
as ordered. sir.

5
00:00:23.024 --> 00:00:24.276
{\an8}[colonel] At ease.

6
00:00:27.779 --> 00:00:28.779
Oh.

7
00:00:29.155 --> 00:00:31.074
{\an8}I believe that's gonna
stick around awhile.

8
00:00:33.034 --> 00:00:36.329
You know. this island is
lousy with sailors. Marines.

9
00:00:37.122 --> 00:00:39.842
You couldn't pick a fight with one
of them instead of two of our own?

10
00:00:41.001 --> 00:00:42.501
[both grunt]

11
00:00:42.502 --> 00:00:45.296
{\an8}Sometimes the fight
picks you. sir.

12
00:00:45.297 --> 00:00:46.897
{\an8}[colonel] What was
the fight even about?

13
00:00:50.635 --> 00:00:52.721
{\an8}I guess I just can't
abide bullies. sir.

14
00:00:53.388 --> 00:00:55.868
{\an8}[colonel] You know. your father
threw a few punches in his day.

15
00:00:56.808 --> 00:00:57.808
Some of them at me.

16
00:00:57.809 --> 00:00:59.101
{\an8}[chuckles]

17
00:00:59.102 --> 00:01:03.439
{\an8}- What do you think he'd make of you now?
- [grunting. groaning]

18
00:01:03.440 --> 00:01:04.440
[Lee] <i>I don't know. sir.</i>

19
00:01:05.317 --> 00:01:07.319
{\an8}Maybe we could sober
him up and ask him.

20
00:01:10.572 --> 00:01:11.947
All right.

21
00:01:11.948 --> 00:01:14.034
{\an8}Well. some orders
have come through.

22
00:01:14.618 --> 00:01:17.579
Security escort for
a Japanese scientist.

23
00:01:18.204 --> 00:01:20.164
[stammers] Sorry. sir.
A Japanese scientist?

24
00:01:20.165 --> 00:01:21.790
[colonel] This isn't a
milk run. Lieutenant.

25
00:01:21.791 --> 00:01:25.085
We already lost a man on
one of these escort missions

26
00:01:25.086 --> 00:01:26.213
a couple of months back.

27
00:01:27.714 --> 00:01:31.217
{\an8}You will protect. observe. and
report when and if able. Understood?

28
00:01:31.218 --> 00:01:32.468
{\an8}Understood. sir.

29
00:01:32.469 --> 00:01:34.679
Then that is all. Lieutenant.

30
00:01:36.973 --> 00:01:37.974
{\an8}Dismissed.

31
00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:45.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

32
00:01:51.321 --> 00:01:55.366
Excuse me. sir. uh. you don't
happen to be Dr. Miura. would...

33
00:01:55.367 --> 00:01:57.244
[speaks Japanese]

34
00:01:57.869 --> 00:01:58.703
Miura?

35
00:01:58.704 --> 00:02:00.747
- [speaks Japanese]
- Oh. sorry.

36
00:02:02.165 --> 00:02:03.333
I think you're here for me.

37
00:02:05.961 --> 00:02:09.004
[chuckles] Wish I could say I was.
but I'm here on army business.

38
00:02:09.506 --> 00:02:11.550
Maybe we can get a drink
on my way out. huh?

39
00:02:12.592 --> 00:02:13.802
[chuckles] Wait a minute.

40
00:02:15.053 --> 00:02:17.263
They told me they were
sending a military escort.

41
00:02:17.264 --> 00:02:19.432
and you're the only
one here in uniform.

42
00:02:21.643 --> 00:02:22.644
Um...

43
00:02:24.104 --> 00:02:25.896
I'm... I'm supposed
to meet a Dr. Miura.

44
00:02:25.897 --> 00:02:27.147
I'm Keiko Miura.

45
00:02:27.148 --> 00:02:30.276
- You're... Keiko. nice to meet you.
- [chuckles] Nice to meet you.

46
00:02:30.277 --> 00:02:31.361
You must be his daughter?

47
00:02:33.363 --> 00:02:34.488
Or...

48
00:02:34.489 --> 00:02:37.992
I'm sorry. I think there's a little
miscommunication happening here.

49
00:02:37.993 --> 00:02:39.868
- Um. let's start over.
- Yes. why don't we?

50
00:02:39.869 --> 00:02:41.245
- Okay.
- You are...

51
00:02:41.246 --> 00:02:44.708
I am Lieutenant Leland Lafayette
Shaw III. but you can call me Lee.

52
00:02:46.293 --> 00:02:49.546
I'm Keiko Miura. and you
may call me Dr. Miura.

53
00:02:59.848 --> 00:03:02.248
[Lee] You know. these things
aren't supposed to go that fast.

54
00:03:02.893 --> 00:03:04.352
[engine revs]

55
00:03:05.645 --> 00:03:06.854
Would you like me to drive?

56
00:03:06.855 --> 00:03:07.939
Why?

57
00:03:08.773 --> 00:03:10.191
Am I making you nervous?

58
00:03:11.234 --> 00:03:12.903
Nope. But. uh.

59
00:03:14.154 --> 00:03:16.322
I've been assigned to you
as your military escort.

60
00:03:16.323 --> 00:03:19.950
This is an army jeep and
I'm. you know. the army.

61
00:03:19.951 --> 00:03:22.119
I've been driving up and
down these roads for weeks.

62
00:03:22.120 --> 00:03:23.203
I know the way.

63
00:03:23.204 --> 00:03:24.289
[engine revs]

64
00:03:25.790 --> 00:03:26.832
[Lee] Okay then.

65
00:03:26.833 --> 00:03:29.553
I'm starting to get the feeling you
don't really want me around here.

66
00:03:31.463 --> 00:03:33.464
Aren't you even curious
why you're here?

67
00:03:33.465 --> 00:03:34.549
Very much so.

68
00:03:36.593 --> 00:03:39.345
[sighs] A WB-29 on a
routine weather mission

69
00:03:39.346 --> 00:03:42.349
scooped up some airborne
radioisotopes over the Philippine Sea.

70
00:03:43.350 --> 00:03:47.144
That's... That's pretty far south for
a Russian bomb test. They don't...

71
00:03:47.145 --> 00:03:49.105
That's because it's
not the Russians.

72
00:03:50.649 --> 00:03:54.235
Well. it's not
us. So. who is it?

73
00:03:54.236 --> 00:03:56.612
Well. they were the wrong
isotopes for bomb fallout.

74
00:03:56.613 --> 00:04:00.658
And meteorological data shows
they likely originated here.

75
00:04:00.659 --> 00:04:01.743
The Philippines?

76
00:04:02.577 --> 00:04:03.617
That's gotta be a mistake.

77
00:04:04.704 --> 00:04:06.039
That's what I'm
here to find out.

78
00:04:07.666 --> 00:04:08.666
Okay.

79
00:04:09.084 --> 00:04:12.045
We should get to work.
Hit the gas. Doc.

80
00:06:02.822 --> 00:06:04.908
[alarm ringing]

81
00:06:09.079 --> 00:06:10.080
[alarm stops]

82
00:06:13.541 --> 00:06:14.793
[exhales sharply]

83
00:06:17.420 --> 00:06:18.421
[sighs]

84
00:06:26.054 --> 00:06:27.055
[sighs]

85
00:07:39.836 --> 00:07:41.421
[screams]

86
00:07:43.381 --> 00:07:44.507
[screams]

87
00:07:45.175 --> 00:07:46.176
[grunts]

88
00:09:17.267 --> 00:09:18.434
[grunts]

89
00:09:18.435 --> 00:09:20.020
Every day the
reading diminishes.

90
00:09:20.562 --> 00:09:23.147
Soon it'll be entirely gone.
and the trail will be lost.

91
00:09:23.148 --> 00:09:25.149
[Lee] Uh-huh. Got
that. Double-time.

92
00:09:25.150 --> 00:09:27.027
- [sighs]
- Your English is very good.

93
00:09:29.279 --> 00:09:31.990
It came in handy when I did my
postgraduate work at Berkeley.

94
00:09:34.576 --> 00:09:35.619
It's impressive.

95
00:09:36.244 --> 00:09:39.038
But. uh. doesn't that make
you a little overqualified

96
00:09:39.039 --> 00:09:40.205
for this snipe hunt?

97
00:09:40.206 --> 00:09:41.707
[Keiko chuckles] This what?

98
00:09:41.708 --> 00:09:43.335
Wild-goose chase.

99
00:09:45.754 --> 00:09:48.339
Come on. Doc. Don't you think
if those readings were legit.

100
00:09:48.340 --> 00:09:50.549
Washington would've sent half
the eggheads at Los Alamos

101
00:09:50.550 --> 00:09:51.550
to check it out?

102
00:09:52.052 --> 00:09:54.637
Not a woman. Certainly
not a Japanese woman.

103
00:09:54.638 --> 00:09:56.056
Oh. you got that right. Yeah.

104
00:09:58.975 --> 00:10:01.477
You want me to lie and pretend
that's not the way things are?

105
00:10:01.478 --> 00:10:02.562
Mm-mmm.

106
00:10:03.855 --> 00:10:05.856
You're telling me you
didn't take one look at me

107
00:10:05.857 --> 00:10:09.194
and make a snap judgment about
who I am the second we met? Huh?

108
00:10:12.280 --> 00:10:15.784
It's not the same. Leland
Lafayette Shaw III.

109
00:10:16.868 --> 00:10:18.787
[sighs] Suppose it's not.

110
00:10:23.541 --> 00:10:24.668
Hmm.

111
00:10:25.877 --> 00:10:26.878
[grunts]

112
00:10:30.590 --> 00:10:31.716
[branch snaps]

113
00:10:38.515 --> 00:10:40.016
[rustling]

114
00:10:41.768 --> 00:10:42.769
Do you hear that?

115
00:10:45.188 --> 00:10:48.108
[branches snapping]

116
00:10:50.068 --> 00:10:51.069
Lieutenant?

117
00:10:55.782 --> 00:10:58.450
- [branches snap]
- [footsteps approaching]

118
00:10:58.451 --> 00:10:59.869
Lieutenant? [sighs]

119
00:11:03.623 --> 00:11:06.751
[person breathes heavily]

120
00:11:08.879 --> 00:11:09.880
Oh.

121
00:11:12.674 --> 00:11:13.675
Hey.

122
00:11:15.427 --> 00:11:16.635
Hey.

123
00:11:16.636 --> 00:11:17.720
[Lee] Don't move.

124
00:11:17.721 --> 00:11:18.888
- Whoa.
- [Keiko] Lieutenant.

125
00:11:18.889 --> 00:11:20.389
- Who are you? Who are you?
- Don't shoot.

126
00:11:20.390 --> 00:11:22.558
I'm American. Navy vet.

127
00:11:22.559 --> 00:11:25.604
And what are you doing here. American
Navy vet. huh? You filming us?

128
00:11:26.730 --> 00:11:28.188
Why? You guys doing
something film worthy?

129
00:11:28.189 --> 00:11:30.482
- I asked you a question.
- I'm just asking a question back.

130
00:11:30.483 --> 00:11:31.734
Well. I got the gun. swab.

131
00:11:31.735 --> 00:11:33.235
so who are you and what
are you doing here?

132
00:11:33.236 --> 00:11:35.238
- Lieutenant.
- My name's William Randa.

133
00:11:36.823 --> 00:11:39.784
Okay. Lieutenant Shaw?

134
00:11:40.410 --> 00:11:41.410
Mm-hmm.

135
00:11:41.411 --> 00:11:45.457
Look. I promise I won't shoot
you if you don't shoot me.

136
00:11:46.124 --> 00:11:47.125
Deal?

137
00:11:55.467 --> 00:11:56.467
All right.

138
00:11:56.468 --> 00:11:57.552
All right?

139
00:11:58.762 --> 00:12:00.804
Still haven't answered my
question. What are you doing here?

140
00:12:00.805 --> 00:12:01.805
[scoffs]

141
00:12:02.307 --> 00:12:07.228
Well. you could say I'm
on a hunting expedition.

142
00:12:07.229 --> 00:12:09.063
I'm a cryptozoologist.

143
00:12:09.064 --> 00:12:13.026
- You're a cryptozoo... Uh. what?
- He studies animals that don't exist.

144
00:12:13.610 --> 00:12:14.611
Yeah.

145
00:12:16.488 --> 00:12:18.782
Atmospheric sampler?
Spectrometer?

146
00:12:19.366 --> 00:12:21.200
- Hey. is this a radiation monitor here?
- Hey. hey. hey.

147
00:12:21.201 --> 00:12:22.618
- [Lee] Easy.
- [Keiko] Don't touch that.

148
00:12:22.619 --> 00:12:24.454
Sorry. I just... I've
never seen one before.

149
00:12:25.205 --> 00:12:27.456
[chuckles] Just wanted
to check it out.

150
00:12:27.457 --> 00:12:30.752
'Cause. uh. it seems like maybe we're
out here hunting for the same thing.

151
00:12:32.128 --> 00:12:33.922
And wh-what's that. Mr. Randa?

152
00:12:35.298 --> 00:12:36.424
The truth.

153
00:13:12.294 --> 00:13:14.296
[cell phone rings]

154
00:13:18.091 --> 00:13:19.717
[Caroline. on phone]
<i>Catey. where have you been?</i>

155
00:13:19.718 --> 00:13:20.718
I'm sorry. I. uh...

156
00:13:20.719 --> 00:13:22.303
[Caroline] <i>I've been
calling and calling you.</i>

157
00:13:22.304 --> 00:13:24.096
Mom. I'm fine. I'm coming home.

158
00:13:24.097 --> 00:13:26.849
[Caroline] <i>Already?
What did you find out?</i>

159
00:13:26.850 --> 00:13:28.559
It doesn't have
anything to do with us.

160
00:13:28.560 --> 00:13:30.811
[Caroline] <i>What does that mean?
What does it have to do...</i>

161
00:13:30.812 --> 00:13:32.689
What did it always have
to do with. Mom? Him.

162
00:13:33.231 --> 00:13:34.273
- [Caroline] <i>Catey.</i>
- [sighs]

163
00:13:34.274 --> 00:13:36.275
- We'll talk when I get home. okay?
- <i>Don't do this.</i>

164
00:13:36.276 --> 00:13:37.777
- Love you. Bye.
- <i>Catey. do not...</i>

165
00:13:44.659 --> 00:13:45.660
American?

166
00:13:47.579 --> 00:13:48.787
Excuse me?

167
00:13:48.788 --> 00:13:50.706
Sorry. I... I didn't mean
to eavesdrop. I just...

168
00:13:50.707 --> 00:13:52.208
I... I overheard your accent.

169
00:13:53.251 --> 00:13:56.587
Sometimes this place can make you feel
like you're stranded on another planet.

170
00:13:56.588 --> 00:13:57.672
Glad I could help.

171
00:14:05.472 --> 00:14:07.348
- Where are you heading?
- Look. I don't mean to be rude.

172
00:14:07.349 --> 00:14:10.351
but I've made all the new friends
I can handle for one day. thanks.

173
00:14:10.352 --> 00:14:12.228
Yeah. Nah. nah. Hey.
I totally get it.

174
00:14:12.229 --> 00:14:16.523
This young woman abroad
runs into a strange man

175
00:14:16.524 --> 00:14:17.609
at the train station.

176
00:14:18.610 --> 00:14:21.488
And next thing you know. you're
buried alive in a coffin somewhere.

177
00:14:24.032 --> 00:14:25.867
I can't imagine
that that helped.

178
00:14:27.035 --> 00:14:29.663
Hey. Wait. wait. wait. Look.
look. look. Hey. I'm harmless.

179
00:14:30.538 --> 00:14:31.915
My name's Tim. [chuckles]

180
00:14:32.499 --> 00:14:34.541
They don't come much more
harmless than the "Tim" variety.

181
00:14:34.542 --> 00:14:35.627
Have a nice night. Tim.

182
00:14:37.128 --> 00:14:38.672
I need to talk to
you about the files.

183
00:14:40.757 --> 00:14:41.758
I don't...

184
00:14:43.468 --> 00:14:44.468
What files?

185
00:14:44.469 --> 00:14:46.221
I work for Monarch.

186
00:14:49.057 --> 00:14:50.141
You're not in trouble.

187
00:14:50.934 --> 00:14:52.434
Not yet.

188
00:14:52.435 --> 00:14:54.688
Those files belong to us.

189
00:14:55.647 --> 00:14:58.149
and they are more important
than you could possibly imagine.

190
00:15:01.987 --> 00:15:03.154
I need to make a call.

191
00:15:04.864 --> 00:15:07.284
Okay. Let's make a call.

192
00:15:25.218 --> 00:15:26.469
All right. All right.

193
00:15:27.304 --> 00:15:28.555
Make your call.

194
00:15:30.307 --> 00:15:31.308
Speaker. please.

195
00:15:32.809 --> 00:15:34.184
Sure. [sighs]

196
00:15:34.185 --> 00:15:35.269
[line rings]

197
00:15:35.270 --> 00:15:37.187
- [Caroline. on phone] <i>Cate? Hello? Cate?</i>
- [grunts]

198
00:15:37.188 --> 00:15:38.772
[groans]

199
00:15:38.773 --> 00:15:39.858
[panting]

200
00:15:43.570 --> 00:15:45.029
[grunting] No.

201
00:15:45.030 --> 00:15:46.364
No. [grunting]

202
00:15:49.784 --> 00:15:52.536
[breathes heavily] I said
you weren't in trouble.

203
00:15:52.537 --> 00:15:54.831
- "Yet". You said "yet."
- [Tim pants]

204
00:16:03.882 --> 00:16:05.841
Look. I swear we're
not gonna hurt you.

205
00:16:05.842 --> 00:16:07.009
[Cate] No. you can't do this.

206
00:16:07.010 --> 00:16:09.470
- I can't let you see where we're going.
- [Cate] No! You don't understand.

207
00:16:09.471 --> 00:16:11.305
I can't breathe.
[panting] I can't...

208
00:16:11.306 --> 00:16:14.808
[hyperventilating] I can't...

209
00:16:14.809 --> 00:16:17.854
[Tim] Relax. You're gonna
be fine. Just breathe. okay?

210
00:16:18.563 --> 00:16:20.898
- [Cate] Let me out. Let me out!
- Calm down. Relax.

211
00:16:20.899 --> 00:16:23.693
- [Cate] Let me out! Let me out!
- [Tim] Relax. Calm down.

212
00:16:25.487 --> 00:16:26.571
Hey! [grunts]

213
00:16:27.489 --> 00:16:29.531
Get her under control. man.

214
00:16:29.532 --> 00:16:30.575
Let me out!

215
00:16:31.743 --> 00:16:33.119
[yelps]

216
00:16:34.621 --> 00:16:36.998
[Cate yelping]

217
00:16:43.338 --> 00:16:45.632
[Cate coughing.
panting. groaning]

218
00:17:00.438 --> 00:17:01.438
[Tim grunts]

219
00:17:10.864 --> 00:17:12.074
[driver breathes heavily]

220
00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:17.288
[breathing heavily]

221
00:17:17.289 --> 00:17:19.373
[panting]

222
00:17:27.924 --> 00:17:28.924
What?

223
00:17:29.509 --> 00:17:31.362
[in Japanese] Why aren't
you answering my texts?

224
00:17:31.386 --> 00:17:33.866
[in English] When's the last time
I answered one of your texts?

225
00:17:34.264 --> 00:17:36.181
[in Japanese] I don't
know... I thought...

226
00:17:36.182 --> 00:17:37.266
[in English] You thought?

227
00:17:37.267 --> 00:17:39.518
You thought that because
of your crazy family drama

228
00:17:39.519 --> 00:17:42.397
that what happened between
us is ancient history?

229
00:17:44.482 --> 00:17:46.067
What do you want from me?

230
00:17:50.113 --> 00:17:52.407
[in Japanese] I found this
in my father's office.

231
00:17:53.742 --> 00:17:55.619
[in English] I do
audio. not home movies.

232
00:17:58.496 --> 00:18:00.123
I told you I was sorry.

233
00:18:01.124 --> 00:18:02.334
Apology accepted.

234
00:18:03.209 --> 00:18:04.209
I'm sorry too.

235
00:18:05.128 --> 00:18:08.297
I... I grabbed onto you to
keep my head above water.

236
00:18:08.298 --> 00:18:09.925
and you didn't wanna
drown. I get it.

237
00:18:15.096 --> 00:18:16.097
You should go home now.

238
00:18:16.681 --> 00:18:17.973
[stammers] Wait. wait. wait.

239
00:18:17.974 --> 00:18:20.559
[stutters] I want those old
computer files we found.

240
00:18:20.560 --> 00:18:21.727
Why?

241
00:18:21.728 --> 00:18:24.855
[stammers] Because they're mine.
What difference does it make to you?

242
00:18:24.856 --> 00:18:26.107
I'm busy.

243
00:18:26.900 --> 00:18:28.026
Come back tomorrow.

244
00:18:33.156 --> 00:18:34.157
[sighs]

245
00:19:04.771 --> 00:19:06.565
[Cate. in Japanese]
She sounded French.

246
00:19:07.482 --> 00:19:10.109
[officer] You said
they were American.

247
00:19:10.110 --> 00:19:11.194
[Cate] The man was.

248
00:19:13.238 --> 00:19:14.239
[officer] Tim?

249
00:19:15.740 --> 00:19:17.909
Do you have some identification?

250
00:19:22.122 --> 00:19:24.457
I lost my bag when I ran away.

251
00:19:25.834 --> 00:19:26.834
My passport...

252
00:19:27.335 --> 00:19:28.753
my phone. all my money.

253
00:19:30.297 --> 00:19:32.591
And you're sure this
wasn't some kind of...

254
00:19:32.883 --> 00:19:34.759
misunderstanding?

255
00:19:36.344 --> 00:19:37.344
What?

256
00:19:38.179 --> 00:19:41.683
Tourists come here to enjoy
what Tokyo has to offer.

257
00:19:43.018 --> 00:19:45.270
The nightlife. Some karaoke.

258
00:19:45.729 --> 00:19:46.771
But...

259
00:19:47.022 --> 00:19:48.440
it's easy to overindulge.

260
00:19:49.608 --> 00:19:51.484
You think I'm drunk?

261
00:19:53.111 --> 00:19:55.322
I was almost kidnapped!

262
00:20:01.411 --> 00:20:03.955
If you feel you are in danger...

263
00:20:05.123 --> 00:20:08.251
I would recommend you
contact the American Embassy.

264
00:20:09.669 --> 00:20:11.046
Wait here.

265
00:20:11.504 --> 00:20:13.048
I will get you the address.

266
00:20:35.862 --> 00:20:37.530
[breathing heavily]

267
00:20:42.077 --> 00:20:43.077
I'm home.

268
00:20:43.286 --> 00:20:44.287
[parent] Welcome back.

269
00:20:53.755 --> 00:20:55.006
Have you had dinner?

270
00:20:55.715 --> 00:20:56.715
I'm not hungry.

271
00:20:56.716 --> 00:20:57.634
[chuckles] You haven't?

272
00:20:57.635 --> 00:20:59.135
I was going to
warm up the curry.

273
00:21:00.554 --> 00:21:01.554
What's this?

274
00:21:02.430 --> 00:21:05.141
[parent] His life was
not easy. you know.

275
00:21:05.850 --> 00:21:08.812
He lost so much
when he was young.

276
00:21:11.690 --> 00:21:13.733
You're defending him?

277
00:21:14.484 --> 00:21:15.569
Aren't you angry?

278
00:21:16.820 --> 00:21:19.823
You're angry. Kentaro.

279
00:21:20.865 --> 00:21:23.243
Do you feel better?

280
00:21:34.379 --> 00:21:36.006
What are you doing?

281
00:21:37.257 --> 00:21:38.300
Now I'm angry too.

282
00:21:40.635 --> 00:21:41.928
Join me. Kentaro.

283
00:21:42.387 --> 00:21:44.014
[exclaims]

284
00:21:44.556 --> 00:21:45.556
[laughs]

285
00:21:45.557 --> 00:21:46.600
Seriously?!

286
00:21:46.975 --> 00:21:48.768
Throw it! [breathes heavily]

287
00:21:49.686 --> 00:21:50.728
- [chuckles]
- [exclaims]

288
00:21:50.729 --> 00:21:51.646
More.

289
00:21:51.647 --> 00:21:52.772
Here.

290
00:21:53.648 --> 00:21:54.983
[exclaims. chuckles]

291
00:21:55.817 --> 00:21:59.321
[breathes heavily. exclaims]

292
00:21:59.988 --> 00:22:01.155
[breathing heavily]

293
00:22:01.156 --> 00:22:03.325
Now we both feel better. right?

294
00:22:05.493 --> 00:22:06.870
[chuckles] A little.

295
00:22:07.621 --> 00:22:08.872
[chuckles]

296
00:22:10.749 --> 00:22:12.417
I'll warm up the curry.

297
00:22:19.758 --> 00:22:20.759
[sighs]

298
00:22:34.981 --> 00:22:37.650
[Billy. in English] So. you guys are
following the radiation. aren't you?

299
00:22:37.651 --> 00:22:38.776
And how do you know about that?

300
00:22:38.777 --> 00:22:41.028
Well. I know you're not
gonna find what's out there

301
00:22:41.029 --> 00:22:42.488
following a Geiger counter.

302
00:22:42.489 --> 00:22:44.406
[Keiko] What should we
be following. Mr. Randa?

303
00:22:44.407 --> 00:22:45.909
Just Billy.

304
00:22:46.660 --> 00:22:49.370
I think you should be following
the stories. Folklore. Legends.

305
00:22:49.371 --> 00:22:52.790
You know. the people of these
mountains. they have an oral tradition

306
00:22:52.791 --> 00:22:56.377
about a dragon that carves a
path of fire across the sky.

307
00:22:56.378 --> 00:22:57.711
Hmm.

308
00:22:57.712 --> 00:23:00.465
Or maybe a path of
ionizing radiation.

309
00:23:02.008 --> 00:23:05.387
So. you're hunting dragons.

310
00:23:06.054 --> 00:23:08.973
[sighs] I told you. I'm
looking for the truth.

311
00:23:08.974 --> 00:23:10.975
That's great. But
we got work to do.

312
00:23:10.976 --> 00:23:12.726
so it's time for you
to hit the trail. bud.

313
00:23:12.727 --> 00:23:14.228
Wait a minute. Lieutenant.

314
00:23:14.229 --> 00:23:16.773
I don't think it's such a bad
idea for Mr. Randa to join us.

315
00:23:17.732 --> 00:23:19.024
I think it's a terrible idea.

316
00:23:19.025 --> 00:23:21.569
[chuckles] You're not here
to think for me. Lieutenant.

317
00:23:21.570 --> 00:23:24.029
- [inhales deeply]
- Look at him. Smell him.

318
00:23:24.030 --> 00:23:25.656
He's probably been lost
out here for weeks.

319
00:23:25.657 --> 00:23:27.283
Hey. hey. I know
exactly where I am. pal.

320
00:23:27.284 --> 00:23:28.659
- Do you?
- Yes.

321
00:23:28.660 --> 00:23:32.037
No. Look. I am here at the behest
of the US Army. and my orders are...

322
00:23:32.038 --> 00:23:34.456
Your orders are to provide me with
whatever assistance I require.

323
00:23:34.457 --> 00:23:38.168
M... My orders are to provide
you with operational security.

324
00:23:38.169 --> 00:23:42.214
and I cannot do that with our new friend.
Billy the jungle hermit. hanging around.

325
00:23:42.215 --> 00:23:43.383
[chuckles] Wow.

326
00:23:44.593 --> 00:23:46.052
[sighs]

327
00:23:47.095 --> 00:23:49.305
Fine. Just go then.

328
00:23:49.306 --> 00:23:51.390
[scoffs] Don't tempt me. Doc.

329
00:23:51.391 --> 00:23:54.268
[scoffs] I didn't ask for you.

330
00:23:54.269 --> 00:23:57.062
I don't need you and
I don't want you.

331
00:23:57.063 --> 00:24:00.942
So. you are relieved of
any responsibility for me.

332
00:24:02.819 --> 00:24:03.987
Dismissed.

333
00:24:07.282 --> 00:24:08.825
I'll send someone
back with the jeep.

334
00:24:13.330 --> 00:24:14.331
[engine starts]

335
00:24:21.129 --> 00:24:22.255
Shall we go?

336
00:24:36.436 --> 00:24:38.687
[Keiko] So. have you
ever seen a dragon?

337
00:24:38.688 --> 00:24:40.147
- [Billy] Once.
- [Keiko] Oh.

338
00:24:40.148 --> 00:24:43.025
[Billy] Well. maybe. It's kind
of why I started doing this.

339
00:24:43.026 --> 00:24:44.777
Trying to prove I'm not crazy.

340
00:24:44.778 --> 00:24:46.153
You think I'm crazy?

341
00:24:46.154 --> 00:24:47.279
I don't even know you.

342
00:24:47.280 --> 00:24:48.698
[sighs] That's true.

343
00:24:49.574 --> 00:24:51.450
Do you often follow strange
men into the jungle?

344
00:24:51.451 --> 00:24:54.411
Uh. this is my
second time today.

345
00:24:54.412 --> 00:24:57.081
- [chuckles. sighs]
- [chuckles]

346
00:24:57.082 --> 00:24:58.416
We call 'em MUTO's.

347
00:24:59.251 --> 00:25:02.503
For Massive Unidentified
Terrestrial Organisms.

348
00:25:02.504 --> 00:25:04.004
- I came up with that.
- Huh.

349
00:25:04.005 --> 00:25:07.675
Terrestrial. So. you don't
think they're space aliens?

350
00:25:07.676 --> 00:25:09.218
You do think I'm crazy.

351
00:25:09.219 --> 00:25:10.719
[sighs] I'm a scientist.

352
00:25:10.720 --> 00:25:12.930
I believe what the evidence
tells me to be true.

353
00:25:12.931 --> 00:25:14.140
- [breathes heavily]
- Okay.

354
00:25:15.141 --> 00:25:18.143
Everyone around here tells
some version of the same story.

355
00:25:18.144 --> 00:25:19.813
- Okay.
- Lights in the sky.

356
00:25:21.439 --> 00:25:24.400
And whatever's making them
has been tracing the same path

357
00:25:24.401 --> 00:25:28.028
over and over and over
again. going back centuries.

358
00:25:28.029 --> 00:25:31.032
- Like comets.
- No. More like migrating birds.

359
00:25:31.950 --> 00:25:32.951
Hold on.

360
00:25:34.035 --> 00:25:36.704
I have to show you
something. [breathes heavily]

361
00:25:36.705 --> 00:25:38.706
These... [inhales sharply] are
the tracks [exhales sharply]

362
00:25:38.707 --> 00:25:41.417
of the radiation readings from
our surveillance aircraft.

363
00:25:41.418 --> 00:25:43.879
[Keiko breathes heavily]

364
00:25:46.798 --> 00:25:47.924
See this?

365
00:25:48.758 --> 00:25:49.759
[breathing heavily]

366
00:25:54.973 --> 00:25:56.933
- [Billy scoffs]
- [Keiko] Incredible.

367
00:25:58.685 --> 00:25:59.686
[exhales sharply]

368
00:26:00.228 --> 00:26:01.813
- This way. This way. Come on.
- Okay.

369
00:26:02.522 --> 00:26:03.647
[Keiko] Where are we going?

370
00:26:03.648 --> 00:26:05.233
[Billy] We're following the map.

371
00:26:14.910 --> 00:26:17.078
[breathing heavily]

372
00:26:18.079 --> 00:26:19.122
We're almost there.

373
00:26:19.789 --> 00:26:21.333
[Keiko] Almost where?

374
00:26:24.294 --> 00:26:25.337
[sighs] What is it?

375
00:26:31.301 --> 00:26:32.469
What is that?

376
00:26:38.016 --> 00:26:39.017
The <i>Lawton.</i>

377
00:27:01.831 --> 00:27:04.167
[breathing shakily]

378
00:27:08.838 --> 00:27:10.840
[breathing shakily]

379
00:27:20.225 --> 00:27:21.225
[Tim] I don't know.

380
00:27:21.226 --> 00:27:22.226
[gasps]

381
00:27:22.227 --> 00:27:23.894
You wanna take a look
and see what's on these.

382
00:27:23.895 --> 00:27:25.730
I have no idea if
they're any good but...

383
00:27:26.439 --> 00:27:27.440
[gasps]

384
00:27:29.401 --> 00:27:30.527
[shushes]

385
00:27:33.530 --> 00:27:34.531
[Duvall] You do it.

386
00:27:49.880 --> 00:27:50.921
[speaks Japanese]

387
00:27:50.922 --> 00:27:55.218
[in Japanese] Hiroshi was eighteen
when his father died in Vietnam.

388
00:27:59.264 --> 00:28:02.392
His Uncle Lee was the
only family he had left.

389
00:28:03.310 --> 00:28:06.313
If they were so close. why
didn't Dad ever mention him?

390
00:28:07.230 --> 00:28:08.230
[sighs]

391
00:28:08.231 --> 00:28:10.066
I think something
happened between them.

392
00:28:11.026 --> 00:28:12.569
He didn't like to talk about

393
00:28:13.320 --> 00:28:15.864
some parts of his life.

394
00:28:17.991 --> 00:28:19.367
Is he still alive?

395
00:28:20.035 --> 00:28:20.869
[sighs]

396
00:28:20.870 --> 00:28:22.037
Oh. I don't know.

397
00:28:23.538 --> 00:28:25.498
This would have been
a long time ago.

398
00:28:26.082 --> 00:28:27.292
[phone chimes]

399
00:28:28.209 --> 00:28:29.335
Sorry.

400
00:28:29.336 --> 00:28:30.336
Mmm.

401
00:28:31.338 --> 00:28:32.756
"CALL ME! IT'S IMPORTANT!"

402
00:28:33.882 --> 00:28:36.634
[doorbell rings]

403
00:28:36.635 --> 00:28:37.843
I'll get it.

404
00:28:37.844 --> 00:28:38.886
Thank you.

405
00:28:38.887 --> 00:28:40.180
[sighs]

406
00:28:47.229 --> 00:28:48.229
Good Evening.

407
00:28:48.647 --> 00:28:50.231
Do you speak English?

408
00:28:50.232 --> 00:28:51.649
[in English. stammers] Yes.

409
00:28:51.650 --> 00:28:53.943
Ah. That's... That's
great. actually.

410
00:28:53.944 --> 00:28:57.112
That makes this much easier...
[inhales sharply] ...for me anyway.

411
00:28:57.113 --> 00:28:58.197
May we come in?

412
00:28:58.198 --> 00:29:01.075
- No. Who are you?
- It's official business.

413
00:29:01.076 --> 00:29:03.869
[stammers] We're with a
special government task force.

414
00:29:03.870 --> 00:29:05.788
- Which government?
- [inhales sharply] You know what?

415
00:29:05.789 --> 00:29:08.499
We'll be in and out
before you even know it.

416
00:29:08.500 --> 00:29:11.627
Wow. You have a lovely
home. [speaks Japanese]

417
00:29:11.628 --> 00:29:13.088
[in Japanese] Who are they?

418
00:29:14.673 --> 00:29:16.273
[in English. stammers]
What do you want?

419
00:29:17.634 --> 00:29:19.093
I want Bill Randa's files.

420
00:29:19.094 --> 00:29:20.386
No. you need to leave.

421
00:29:20.387 --> 00:29:22.805
No. you need to hand
over those files.

422
00:29:22.806 --> 00:29:25.891
Otherwise. you. your friends.

423
00:29:25.892 --> 00:29:28.228
and your mother are gonna
be in a lot of trouble.

424
00:29:28.603 --> 00:29:29.479
[parent] Kentaro...?

425
00:29:29.479 --> 00:29:30.479
[in Japanese] It's okay.

426
00:29:30.981 --> 00:29:33.650
There's something
that your son stole.

427
00:29:35.235 --> 00:29:37.195
He's going to have
to come with us.

428
00:29:37.821 --> 00:29:39.029
[stutters]

429
00:29:39.030 --> 00:29:40.030
Is it true?

430
00:29:40.282 --> 00:29:42.116
Did you take
something of theirs?

431
00:29:42.117 --> 00:29:43.576
They say I stole some files.

432
00:29:43.577 --> 00:29:44.786
Enough.

433
00:29:45.036 --> 00:29:46.413
Let's have it.

434
00:29:47.163 --> 00:29:52.127
If he returns whatever he
took. will you leave him alone?

435
00:29:52.711 --> 00:29:53.711
Of course.

436
00:29:54.504 --> 00:29:55.630
[exhales sharply]

437
00:29:56.214 --> 00:29:57.966
[inhales sharply.
speaks Japanese]

438
00:29:58.550 --> 00:30:00.385
If you have what they
are looking for...

439
00:30:01.052 --> 00:30:02.512
you should give it to them.

440
00:30:03.179 --> 00:30:04.222
Are you sure?

441
00:30:04.556 --> 00:30:05.557
[sighs]

442
00:30:06.933 --> 00:30:09.603
It must be very important.

443
00:30:15.275 --> 00:30:16.276
[in English] I'll get it.

444
00:30:17.736 --> 00:30:20.487
Amazing. [stammers] Thank
you. [clears throat]

445
00:30:20.488 --> 00:30:23.074
Tea? You like tea?

446
00:30:24.075 --> 00:30:25.159
Tea?

447
00:30:25.160 --> 00:30:26.827
[Tim] Uh. no.
We're good. Thanks.

448
00:30:26.828 --> 00:30:29.268
[in Japanese] I hope my son
hasn't caused any trouble for you.

449
00:30:29.873 --> 00:30:31.373
He's a good man now.

450
00:30:31.374 --> 00:30:34.002
but when he was younger
there were so many problems!

451
00:30:34.711 --> 00:30:36.587
- So much drinking!
- [in English] Hurry up!

452
00:30:36.588 --> 00:30:39.174
[in Japanese] I wanted
him to find a nice girl.

453
00:30:39.883 --> 00:30:41.676
Someone to settle him down.

454
00:30:42.260 --> 00:30:44.261
You are very attractive.

455
00:30:44.262 --> 00:30:45.597
Are you single?

456
00:30:49.476 --> 00:30:51.352
- [in English] Oh. shit.
- [door slams]

457
00:30:51.353 --> 00:30:53.687
- Shit.
- Kentaro!

458
00:30:53.688 --> 00:30:55.649
- [banging on door]
- [Tim] Open up!

459
00:30:55.857 --> 00:30:57.400
[in Japanese] Kentaro. run!

460
00:31:38.525 --> 00:31:39.776
[phone chimes]

461
00:31:46.533 --> 00:31:47.866
[Keiko] You know this ship?

462
00:31:47.867 --> 00:31:49.286
[Billy] USS <i>Lawton.</i>

463
00:31:50.245 --> 00:31:53.498
Went down 200 miles
west of Pearl in 1943.

464
00:31:54.124 --> 00:31:55.500
Pearl Harbor?

465
00:31:56.293 --> 00:31:58.669
That's 5.000 miles from here.

466
00:31:58.670 --> 00:31:59.754
Exactly.

467
00:32:01.047 --> 00:32:02.549
[Billy exhales deeply]

468
00:32:07.721 --> 00:32:10.390
[ship creaks]

469
00:32:17.439 --> 00:32:18.607
[Keiko] Is this safe?

470
00:32:29.618 --> 00:32:30.785
Mr. Randa.

471
00:32:31.745 --> 00:32:34.788
You said you study
myths. stories.

472
00:32:34.789 --> 00:32:37.667
I'm interested in why people
tell the stories they tell.

473
00:32:42.464 --> 00:32:44.089
[Billy] What inspired
the storyteller.

474
00:32:44.090 --> 00:32:48.511
- [ship creaks. rumbles]
- [gasps. breathing shakily]

475
00:32:51.848 --> 00:32:52.848
What terrified 'em.

476
00:32:52.849 --> 00:32:54.809
[breathing shakily]

477
00:33:11.409 --> 00:33:12.410
[Keiko] What is it?

478
00:33:14.829 --> 00:33:17.582
Mr. Randa. Maybe we
should stick together...

479
00:33:22.796 --> 00:33:24.464
[grunts]

480
00:33:26.675 --> 00:33:27.884
[sighs]

481
00:33:32.973 --> 00:33:33.974
[Keiko] Mr. Randa.

482
00:33:36.810 --> 00:33:37.811
Billy.

483
00:33:39.854 --> 00:33:41.106
{\an8}[sighs]

484
00:33:47.612 --> 00:33:49.155
You were on this ship.

485
00:33:52.867 --> 00:33:53.868
Yeah.

486
00:33:57.289 --> 00:33:58.999
Is this what you
were looking for?

487
00:33:59.666 --> 00:34:01.167
Did you know it was here?

488
00:34:05.130 --> 00:34:06.131
Did I know?

489
00:34:10.969 --> 00:34:12.178
Let's say hoped.

490
00:34:15.181 --> 00:34:16.266
Not very scientific.

491
00:34:18.809 --> 00:34:21.688
[sighs] I know we hit something
in the water that night.

492
00:34:22.355 --> 00:34:24.024
We figured it was
a Japanese sub.

493
00:34:26.276 --> 00:34:29.153
[sighs] The whole ship went
down in less than three minutes.

494
00:34:30.822 --> 00:34:31.907
Who else survived?

495
00:34:36.494 --> 00:34:37.495
Only me.

496
00:34:53.470 --> 00:34:56.431
[Geiger counter whirring]

497
00:35:41.601 --> 00:35:42.810
[in Japanese] Going to the back.

498
00:35:42.811 --> 00:35:43.895
Okay.

499
00:36:00.245 --> 00:36:01.955
[in English] Who are
you? Jason Bourne?

500
00:36:03.456 --> 00:36:05.667
You're from San Francisco.
You were there that day.

501
00:36:06.251 --> 00:36:07.459
You don't have a bag packed.

502
00:36:07.460 --> 00:36:09.795
ready to head for higher ground
when the tide starts rising?

503
00:36:09.796 --> 00:36:12.924
Yeah. It's full of bottled water
and batteries. not extra passports.

504
00:36:16.720 --> 00:36:18.305
- May.
- Hey. are you okay?

505
00:36:19.097 --> 00:36:20.639
What is she doing here?

506
00:36:20.640 --> 00:36:22.517
Hey. Whoa. She's in this too.

507
00:36:24.686 --> 00:36:25.978
Somebody's after those files.

508
00:36:25.979 --> 00:36:27.563
Why don't we just give
'em what they want?

509
00:36:27.564 --> 00:36:29.773
[scoffs] Maybe then they'll
leave all of us alone.

510
00:36:29.774 --> 00:36:31.483
Okay. yeah. Good luck with that.

511
00:36:31.484 --> 00:36:32.818
What's your plan? Just run?

512
00:36:32.819 --> 00:36:35.362
Me? I have contacts. I
can get us fake passports.

513
00:36:35.363 --> 00:36:37.907
I don't want a fake passport.
I want my real passport.

514
00:36:37.908 --> 00:36:39.199
I haven't done anything wrong.

515
00:36:39.200 --> 00:36:41.285
Okay. When have people in
power ever cared about...

516
00:36:41.286 --> 00:36:42.370
Hold on.

517
00:36:44.247 --> 00:36:45.457
I know where to go.

518
00:36:47.250 --> 00:36:48.585
Trust me.

519
00:36:49.753 --> 00:36:50.754
Come on.

520
00:36:58.303 --> 00:37:00.722
- [Keiko] What is that?
- [Billy] I don't know.

521
00:37:02.724 --> 00:37:05.143
[Billy sighs] Looks organic.

522
00:37:28.583 --> 00:37:29.793
[Billy gasps. exclaims]

523
00:37:31.211 --> 00:37:33.630
Oh... [groans. pants]

524
00:37:35.423 --> 00:37:36.424
Oh. God.

525
00:37:41.471 --> 00:37:42.806
[Keiko] There are so many.

526
00:37:46.810 --> 00:37:49.020
[inhales shakily] When did
you say this ship sank?

527
00:37:50.272 --> 00:37:51.481
Nine years ago.

528
00:37:54.234 --> 00:37:56.151
I think I've seen everything
I need to in here.

529
00:37:56.152 --> 00:37:57.404
Yeah.

530
00:38:04.536 --> 00:38:08.038
[breathes heavily] That
wasn't there before.

531
00:38:08.039 --> 00:38:09.833
- [Billy] This is fresh.
- Fresh what?

532
00:38:10.500 --> 00:38:12.418
We'll find another
way outta here.

533
00:38:12.419 --> 00:38:14.044
- How did it get here?
- [grunts]

534
00:38:14.045 --> 00:38:15.880
Is there something in
here that's making it...

535
00:38:15.881 --> 00:38:17.257
I don't know. Come on.

536
00:38:37.652 --> 00:38:39.153
[in Japanese] You're
here to see the Colonel?

537
00:38:39.154 --> 00:38:41.156
Yes. we are.

538
00:38:41.823 --> 00:38:43.543
[in Japanese. stammers]
If he's still alive.

539
00:38:43.867 --> 00:38:45.744
So. we can see the Colonel?

540
00:39:07.724 --> 00:39:09.017
[in English] Colonel Shaw?

541
00:39:22.489 --> 00:39:23.490
What's your name?

542
00:39:24.783 --> 00:39:25.784
Kentaro.

543
00:39:26.284 --> 00:39:27.326
Kentaro what?

544
00:39:27.327 --> 00:39:28.411
Randa.

545
00:39:28.912 --> 00:39:34.625
[inhales deeply] Oh. my God.
[chuckles] You're Hiroshi's boy.

546
00:39:34.626 --> 00:39:36.377
[Lee inhales deeply]

547
00:39:36.378 --> 00:39:37.962
[stammers] And you?

548
00:39:37.963 --> 00:39:40.507
I'm Cate Randa.

549
00:39:41.216 --> 00:39:42.300
Course you are.

550
00:39:45.387 --> 00:39:48.472
I. uh... I didn't know
Hiroshi even had a daughter.

551
00:39:48.473 --> 00:39:50.641
[Cate scoffs] Well. I
didn't know he had a son.

552
00:39:50.642 --> 00:39:53.270
Turns out he was good
at keeping secrets.

553
00:39:57.232 --> 00:39:59.234
[chuckles] Not my
drama. No relation.

554
00:40:00.151 --> 00:40:02.696
- We wanted to ask you about our fa...
- W-Why don't we. um...

555
00:40:05.282 --> 00:40:06.283
Yeah. Come on.

556
00:40:07.492 --> 00:40:08.493
Let's get some air.

557
00:40:09.494 --> 00:40:10.620
Come on.

558
00:40:15.709 --> 00:40:19.044
If you guys could just kinda keep
your voices down. that'd be good.

559
00:40:19.045 --> 00:40:20.630
Tell me. how'd you get here?

560
00:40:21.464 --> 00:40:22.464
Rented a minivan.

561
00:40:22.465 --> 00:40:25.844
That's good. But I mean.
how did you find me?

562
00:40:26.678 --> 00:40:27.678
My mom.

563
00:40:27.679 --> 00:40:29.264
- Emiko.
- Yes.

564
00:40:30.765 --> 00:40:31.766
[chuckles]

565
00:40:34.019 --> 00:40:35.603
We found something
in my father's safe.

566
00:40:35.604 --> 00:40:37.313
- Kentaro.
- What? He's my great uncle Lee.

567
00:40:37.314 --> 00:40:39.356
What did you find in the safe?

568
00:40:39.357 --> 00:40:40.733
Old computer files.

569
00:40:40.734 --> 00:40:43.235
Bunch of crazy
shit. Monster shit.

570
00:40:43.236 --> 00:40:47.407
[shushes] Can you please.
please keep your voices down?

571
00:40:48.700 --> 00:40:51.952
What's this all about? Why are you
here? And you gotta make it kinda quick.

572
00:40:51.953 --> 00:40:54.122
We wanna find out what
happened to my father.

573
00:40:55.248 --> 00:40:56.249
[stammers] You tell me.

574
00:40:57.542 --> 00:41:00.419
Right after G-Day. he said he
had someplace he needed to go.

575
00:41:00.420 --> 00:41:01.587
Wouldn't tell us where.

576
00:41:01.588 --> 00:41:03.505
but a week later we were
told the plane he was on

577
00:41:03.506 --> 00:41:05.341
disappeared somewhere in Alaska.

578
00:41:05.342 --> 00:41:07.886
[scoffs] Turns out he had a
whole secret life in Japan.

579
00:41:08.929 --> 00:41:10.512
I came here to try
and figure it out.

580
00:41:10.513 --> 00:41:13.015
but now we're being chased by
these Monarch people and. uh...

581
00:41:13.016 --> 00:41:15.976
"Disappeared"? As in. no body?

582
00:41:15.977 --> 00:41:17.562
<i>No death certificate?</i>

583
00:41:18.438 --> 00:41:20.565
- What are you saying?
- Hey.

584
00:41:21.233 --> 00:41:23.609
Hey. w-what is this place? Huh?

585
00:41:23.610 --> 00:41:28.822
Oh. this place is what Monarch
euphemistically refers to

586
00:41:28.823 --> 00:41:30.867
as "secure asset management."

587
00:41:32.118 --> 00:41:33.577
Right. So. you're
imprisoned here.

588
00:41:33.578 --> 00:41:35.412
Okay. Well. we're leaving. Mmm.

589
00:41:35.413 --> 00:41:37.915
Yeah. you can try. but they're
just gonna keep following you

590
00:41:37.916 --> 00:41:41.503
and following you and following you.
until they finally get what they want.

591
00:41:42.003 --> 00:41:43.003
Or?

592
00:41:43.004 --> 00:41:44.381
Well. that's up to you.

593
00:41:44.965 --> 00:41:47.383
Now. you can choke down that
mountain of Monarch bullshit

594
00:41:47.384 --> 00:41:49.886
about your father
disappearing without a trace.

595
00:41:53.515 --> 00:41:56.600
Or... [sighs] ...we can get
the hell outta here right now

596
00:41:56.601 --> 00:41:58.937
and find out what really
happened with your dad.

597
00:41:59.521 --> 00:42:00.521
[grunts]

598
00:42:03.066 --> 00:42:05.735
Now you got just about 60
seconds to make up your minds.

599
00:42:10.949 --> 00:42:12.158
What's it gonna be?

600
00:42:19.666 --> 00:42:20.708
Here. this way.

601
00:42:20.709 --> 00:42:22.042
[Keiko] Are you sure?

602
00:42:22.043 --> 00:42:25.379
I did two tours in this tin
can. Doc. [breathes deeply]

603
00:42:25.380 --> 00:42:26.505
[exhales sharply]

604
00:42:26.506 --> 00:42:27.882
[growling]

605
00:42:27.883 --> 00:42:29.426
[gasps] What is that?

606
00:42:33.680 --> 00:42:36.349
- Let's keep it moving. Come on.
- [Keiko] Okay.

607
00:42:38.643 --> 00:42:40.102
- [growling]
- [Billy] Whoa!

608
00:42:40.103 --> 00:42:41.186
[Keiko] Are you all right?

609
00:42:41.187 --> 00:42:42.938
[Billy] Oh. Jesus Christ.

610
00:42:42.939 --> 00:42:44.982
- Go back! Go!
- [pants] Oh. my God.

611
00:42:44.983 --> 00:42:47.401
[panting]

612
00:42:47.402 --> 00:42:49.695
[grunts. screams] Oh. my God!

613
00:42:49.696 --> 00:42:50.989
No.

614
00:42:51.823 --> 00:42:53.073
- [groans]
- Hang on!

615
00:42:53.074 --> 00:42:56.452
[grunts. screaming]

616
00:42:56.453 --> 00:42:58.370
[Keiko] It's leaving!
Now's our chance!

617
00:42:58.371 --> 00:43:00.873
[groaning]

618
00:43:00.874 --> 00:43:02.333
- Push!
- I am pushing!

619
00:43:02.334 --> 00:43:04.501
- [Keiko] Come on!
- [Billy yells. grunts]

620
00:43:04.502 --> 00:43:06.671
Where'd it go? [groans]

621
00:43:08.965 --> 00:43:10.216
- [Billy] Help!
- [groans]

622
00:43:10.217 --> 00:43:11.300
[Billy] Hurry!

623
00:43:11.301 --> 00:43:13.010
What the hell is going on?

624
00:43:13.011 --> 00:43:15.430
- [Keiko] Help! Help!
- [Billy] Come on!

625
00:43:16.223 --> 00:43:18.098
- Watch out!
- Holy shit!

626
00:43:18.099 --> 00:43:19.851
[grunts. pants]

627
00:43:21.311 --> 00:43:23.104
Oh! Oh. my God!

628
00:43:23.688 --> 00:43:24.980
Oh. my God!

629
00:43:24.981 --> 00:43:26.148
Help me get him out!

630
00:43:26.149 --> 00:43:28.525
- [panting]
- Come on! Before it comes back!

631
00:43:28.526 --> 00:43:30.069
Okay. [grunts]

632
00:43:30.070 --> 00:43:31.237
Here we go.

633
00:43:31.238 --> 00:43:32.529
One. two. three.

634
00:43:32.530 --> 00:43:34.281
[straining]

635
00:43:34.282 --> 00:43:36.242
[grunts] It's too heavy.

636
00:43:36.243 --> 00:43:37.534
[groaning]

637
00:43:37.535 --> 00:43:40.120
I'm gonna stick this under.
and we're all gonna lift. okay?

638
00:43:40.121 --> 00:43:41.121
- Okay.
- [Billy grunts]

639
00:43:41.122 --> 00:43:42.998
One. two. three.

640
00:43:42.999 --> 00:43:47.503
Go! [grunts] Get up! Get up! Get
up! Get up! Billy! Hey. get up!

641
00:43:47.504 --> 00:43:48.879
[panting. groaning]

642
00:43:48.880 --> 00:43:51.258
- [Lee] Go! Go. go. go!
- [Keiko] Okay. okay.

643
00:43:55.470 --> 00:43:57.430
- [grunts. pants]
- Go!

644
00:43:58.056 --> 00:44:00.891
[grunts] Go. go. go!

645
00:44:00.892 --> 00:44:04.145
[panting. grunting]

646
00:44:05.313 --> 00:44:06.605
[panting]

647
00:44:06.606 --> 00:44:10.401
- [panting]
- [growling]

648
00:44:10.402 --> 00:44:11.986
Go! Go. go. go. go!

649
00:44:11.987 --> 00:44:13.488
[panting]

650
00:44:16.449 --> 00:44:18.868
[shrieking]

651
00:44:21.329 --> 00:44:23.707
[panting. grunting]

652
00:44:24.624 --> 00:44:26.125
[panting]

653
00:44:26.126 --> 00:44:27.626
[dragon shrieking]

654
00:44:27.627 --> 00:44:28.962
Oh. my God.

655
00:44:29.546 --> 00:44:31.381
[pants] It is a dragon.

656
00:44:32.299 --> 00:44:34.592
[dragon shrieking]

657
00:44:34.593 --> 00:44:35.677
[groans]

658
00:44:36.261 --> 00:44:37.845
[pants]

659
00:44:37.846 --> 00:44:40.640
[panting]

660
00:44:47.022 --> 00:44:50.066
It's... [pants] ...incredible.

661
00:44:54.988 --> 00:44:56.615
[dragon shrieking]

662
00:44:58.700 --> 00:45:02.579
[shrieking]

662
00:45:03.305 --> 00:46:03.315
